*Add/Update Address*

CALL : `/user/updateAddress`
METHOD : POST

PARAMS :

```'id'            => 'sometimes|exists:addresses,id',
'address_type'  => 'required', (1=> shipping address, 2=> billing address)
'postal_code'   => 'required|regex:/^[A-Z0-9^]+$/',
'state_id'      => 'required|exists:states,id',
'city_id'       => 'required|exists:cities,id',
'name'          => 'required',
'address'       => 'required',
'mobile_number' => 'required',
'is_default'    => 'required' (true/false)```

1) you can add/update saved address from this one call. if you will pass `id` with address, it will assume it as a update call. else it will create a new address.
2) `state_id` and `city_id` are required from our database records which you will get from common configuration call. if you will pass wrong ids, it will not accept.

*Common Configuration*

CALL : `/common/commonConfiguration`
METHOD: GET

PARAMS :
```
```
1) this is common call which can be called without authentication or with authentication. you will get all records related to states, cities, attributes and some common settings from this call.
2) take `state_id` and `city_id` from this configuration as a dropdown.


*Favourite/Unfavourite Product*

CALL : `/product/favUnfavProduct`
METHOD: POST

PARAMS :
```id:{productId}
is_fav:false/true```


1) this will be called to add/remove product from favourite list. once you will add product in favourite list. you will get `is_fav:true` in any product call. show in listing if product is already added into favourite. if it isn't in favourite list. give it a button to add in a favourite list.